  "response": "Steam is often used to produce mechanical energy through a process involving turbines in power plants. When water is heated to create steam, the steam's high pressure and temperature can be directed to move the blades of a turbine. This mechanical energy generated by the turbine can then be converted into electrical energy using a generator. Therefore, steam is primarily used to generate mechanical energy, which is subsequently converted into electrical energy.",
